Had a good cafe conversation with a friend recently about the dying of nightlife in many places and recalled Dr. Broda Barnes' description of a person with good thyroid function as someone who wants to go dance until 2-3 AM and then has no problem going to work the next morning.

He said it in the context of hypothyroid people usually marrying other hypothyroid people because if your thyroid is not working you want to go home early from the dances and get enough sleep if you have to get up early and go to work. Most people today couldn't handle even this.

Buck Tow Truck was talking about how if you're doing the 20 rep squats routine you get a type of fatigue that's different from the heavy 5 rep sets one, I think it's that exercise-induced systemic serotonin malaise Haidut talked about that can be turned off with Cyproheptadine...

Probably a good idea to pop half a mg Cypro if you're doing the 20 rep squats routine if you can work through the drowsiness the first week or so, all serious hardcore lifters have done it at least once even though it gets genuinely brutal. Bugenhagen also did it back in the day.

I think it's time for Mexican regional culture to become globally known similarly to how people on the internet know little stuff about the US like the Midwest being cozy or Appalachia being eerie etc. The world should know what Chihuahua is like or the stereotypes about Yucatan.

Like people in Europe and Asia already have these ideas about US regional lore like LA being cursed and weird or NYC being full of fashionable layabouts, the same should be true for Mexico, we must know what the people are in each big city or state. The Mexicans must tell us.
